The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The consistency of the revolution counter value must be checked. If this is not possible, the axis must be referenced. Bit 11: MPos2 Bit 12: MSystem : An M System error message signals that a multiturn-related internal error during the initialization phase of the encoder has occurred. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The power-on cycle should be repeated. If this also fails, a hardware problem of the encoder is probable. The consistency of the revolution counter value must also be checked. Bit 13: MPowerFailure : The M Power failure error message signalizes that both the voltage of the buffer battery (UBAT) and the main supply voltage (UP) have fallen below the defined limit values. The subsequent electronics can only read out this error message when the main voltage supply has been restored. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not defined and therefore faulty. During the M Power failure state there is no revolution counting. The possibly simultaneously occurring error messages M Pos 1, M System and M Overflow are to be ignored. Corrective measure: The axis must be referenced again. Bit 14: MOverflow : The M Overflow error message signals that the specified (multiturn) counting range of the encoder has been exceeded. The encoder remains fully functional. M Overflow error messages can only be cleared when the multiturn value is again in the specified counting range. Corrective measure: Bring the axis into the specified counting range of the encoder again and clear error messages according to the EnDat specification. Bit 15: MBattery

The encoder could not transmit a valid position. Id=0x%01: Position status signals an error. Arg='Position Status'
'Position Status' Bit 0: ChannelEnable Bit 1: Error, Internal error occured, reported by ic-haus IPCore. Bit 2: PosReady, Position received and shifted, ready to be read by drive. Bit 3: EncReady, Set once the ic-haus IPCore has been set up and is running. No evaluation of encoder's answers or correctnes of configuration. Bit 4: LastPosValid, Position in last communication cycle was valid. Bit 5: PosValid , Combinated evaluation of Bits -Error (Bit 1 of this status) -nAGSError (Bit 9 of this status) -Position valid from ic-haus core (position received, CRC validated, Bit 12 of this status) -nSCDError (Bit 8 of this status) Bit 6: Bit 7: Bit 8: Bit 9: Bit 10: Bit 11: Bit 12: Bit 13: Bit 14: Bit 15:

The encoder could not transmit a valid position. Id=0x%01: Position status signals an error. Arg='Position Status'
'Position Status' Bit 0: ChannelEnable Bit 1: Error, Internal error occured, reported by ic-haus IPCore. Bit 2: PosReady, Position received and shifted, ready to be read by drive. Bit 3: EncReady, Set once the ic-haus IPCore has been set up and is running. No evaluation of encoder's answers or correctnes of configuration. Bit 4: LastPosValid, Position in last communication cycle was valid. Bit 5: PosValid, Combinated evaluation of Bits -Error (Bit 1 of this status) -nAGSError (Bit 9 of this status) -Position valid from ic-haus core (position received, CRC validated, Bit 12 of this status) -nSCDError (Bit 8 of this status) Bit 6: REGEND, Register Communication, not used Bit 7: nREGERR, Register Communication, not used Bit 8: nSCDERR , An error in the single cycle data detected by checksum verification (CRC) is shown with nSCDERR. If a sensor data error is signaled, the faulty sensor can be verified by reading SVALIDx. The nSCDERR flag is set after power on and after executing INIT. Bit 9: nAGSERR, An AGS watchdog error nAGSERR is set during the automatic transmission of sensor data enabled by the instruction bit AGS if no new cycle could be initiated. If the last BiSS frame has not been finished in time, the next BiSS frame will be omitted. The following BiSS frame will be executed if possible. The nAGSERR flag is set when resetting the instruction bit AGS (typically by writing BREAK into the instruction register. (We do not use AGS, but the signal is misbehaving sometimes) Bit 10: EOT, End Of Transmission, no encoder communication currently active Bit 11: SLO_line_state, Current Status of SL, directly measured at the line, no core required. Bit 12: SVALID1, The CRC verification result of the received single cycle sensor data of every BiSS frame is written to the validity message register SVALID for each slave separately. If the CRC is disabled in the slave configuration the correspondent SVALID flag is set after the reading of the sensor data is complete. After reading the sensor data, it is recommended to reset the validity flags by writing to the SVALID register. This way, it is possible to recognize updated sensor data. Bit 13: rsvd : 1; Bit 14: SenseData0, Bit 0 of received data, should be ENCODER WARNING in all BiSS-C encoders. Bit 15: SenseData1, Bit 1 of received data, should be ENCODER ERROR in all BiSS-C encoders.

Event.Message: No errors
Continuous over current (device output side), Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The demanded current from axis system exceeds permanently the nominal current by more than the nominal current.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Your applikation is so designed, that this exceeds permanently the allowed value.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analize your application and make that this overcurrent does not happen. E.g. make that not so many motors run with so much current at once. Or use a bigger power supply module.

Event.Message: Peak over current (device output side), Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The demanded current from axis system overloads the power supply module. This happens when a current of two times the nominal current is requested for longer than 5s.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Your applikation is so designed, that this exceeds the maximal allowed current.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analize your application and make that this overcurrent does not happen. E.g. make that not so many motors accelerate with so much current at once. Or use a bigger power supply module.

Event.Message: Continuous over current (device output side)

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The demanded current from axis system exceeds parametrized warning threshold.

Event.Message: Mains over-voltage, Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The actual mains voltage exceeds the parametrized mains voltage (0x8000:06) by more than 20% or by more than the parametrized positive tolerance (0x8000:07), if this higher than 20%.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The actual mains voltage is too high.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Look for a allowed mains voltage.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The positive mains voltage tolerance (0x8000:07) is parametrized too low.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Correct this parametrized value.

Event.Message: Phase failure, Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: One phase is failed by 3-phase-supply.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The mains voltage supply is faulty.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analyze the mains voltage supply and resolve the problem.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The mains voltage supply is disturbed over and over.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Activate a filter, which effects, that the phase monitoring waits longer, until this error is set.

CauseRemedy.Cause: You use the power supply module in a one-phase-mains but it is parametrized for three phases. And the module has not recognized the mains type properly.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the parameter Mains type (0x8000:04) and correct its value. Switch on again the mains voltage.

Event.Message: Mains voltage over brake resistor operating voltage. Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The mains voltage has voltage peaks, which makes that the brake chopper gets switched on.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Voltage peaks occur by the mains voltage.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analize the mains supply and make, that the voltage peaks do not happen.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The parametrization of DC link max voltage (0x8000:01) is too low.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your application and parametrize the DC link max voltage higher, if necessary. In this case the switchOn threshold voltage (0x9006:0C) of the brake chopper should has been changed.

Event.Message: Wrong mains type. Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The connected mains type (3Ph/AC, 1Ph/AC or DC) does not match with parametrized value of Mains type (0x8000:04).

CauseRemedy.Cause: Mains type (0x8000:04) is parametrized with wrong value.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the parameter Mains type (0x8000:04) and correct its value.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The mains supply is not connected right.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the mains suppy and connected it right, Switch on the mains voltage again.

Event.Message: Mains over-voltage

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The connected mains voltage exceeds the parametrized warning threshold.

Event.Message: Mains under-voltage

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The connected mains voltage fell below the parametrized warning threshold.

Event.Message: DC link over-voltage, Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The DC link voltage rises over the permitted DC link voltage because of power feedback (brake) from the motors.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Your application is so designed, that the permitted DC link voltage is exceeded.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analize your application and make, that this overvoltage can not happen.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The parametrization of DC link max voltage (0x8000:01) is too low.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your application and parametrize the DC link max voltage (0x8000:01) higher, if necessary.

Event.Message: Device DC link over-voltage, Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The DC link voltage rises over the permitted maximal DC link voltage because of power feedback (brake) from the motors.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Your application is so designed, that the permitted maximal DC link voltage is exceeded.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analize your application and make, that this overvoltage can not happen.

CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analize your application and make, that this thermic overload does not happen.

Event.Message: Read failure EEPROM Pcb ID {0}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: A error by reading data from the eeprom happened by the initialization. This error by initializing operating time is deactivated by following firmware: - v1.01 b0002 - v1.01 b0001 - v0.32 b0004

CauseRemedy.Cause: An internal hard- or software failure happened, while reading data from eeprom.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your competent Beckhoff office.

Event.Message: Parameter 0x{0,x}/{1,x} with parametrized 0x{2,x}/{3,x} is too low

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Value of first parameter is too low by value of second parameter.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Parametrized DC link max voltage (0x8000:01) is too low for parametrized mains voltage (0x8000:06).
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Look at the internal calculated values 0x9006:0C and 0x9006:0E. The first one must be higher than second one. Parametrize 0x8000:01 and 0x8000:06 again, so that this is achieved.

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Value of first parameter is too high by value of second parameter.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Parametrized mains voltage min tolerance (0x8000:08) is too high for parametrized mains voltage (0x8000:06).
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Parametrize 0x8000:08 or 0x8000:06 so that the value of object 0x9006:0F is not exceeded.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Parametrized mains voltage max tolerance (0x8000:07) is too high for parametrized mains voltage (0x8000:06).
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Parametrize 0x8000:07 or 0x8000:06 so that the value of object 0x9006:0E is not exceeded.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Parametrized mains voltage (0x8000:06) is too high for parametrized mains mains type (0x8000:04).
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Parametrize 0x8000:07 or 0x8000:06 so that the value of object 0x9006:0E is not exceeded.

Event.Message: Value of parameter 0x{0,x}/{1,x} not supported
Failure brake chopper, Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Brake chopper failured.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Brake chopper is damaged.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your competent Beckhoff office.

Event.Message: Over current brake chopper, Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Your connected brake resistor (internal or external) was overloaded.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Current at connected brake resistor is too high. The brake resistor may be damaged.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Check whether your brake resistor is damaged, if external one connected. Try to operate power supply module again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your competent Beckhoff office.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Your applikation is so designed, that this exceeds the maximal allowed current at the brake resistor.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analize your application and make that this overcurrent does not happen.

Event.Message: Brake resistor not found. Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: No connected brake resistor could be detected.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Internal brake resistor is faulty and any external brake resistor has not been connected.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your competent Beckhoff office.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The connection bridge for the internal brake resistor is missing and any external brake resistor has not been connected.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Plug in the connection bridge or connect an external brake resistor.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The connection bridge for the internal brake resistor is not pugged in, an external brake resistor has been connected but this may be damaged.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your external brake resistor. If this is not damaged, try to operate the power supply module again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your competent Beckhoff office.

Event.Message: Brake resistor power overload by DC link over-voltage. Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Brake resistor was disabled because of power overload. As result over-voltage at dc link.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Your application is so designed, that a dc link overvoltage overloads the brake resistor.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analize your application and make, that this overload does not happen.

Event.Message: Wrong xml file. Operating time counter: {0} s., Entry counter: {1}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Device description file does not match to device or to firmware.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Wrong file by firmware update choosen.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Start again a firmware update with the right file.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Wrong file by device description update choosen.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Start again a firmware update with the right file. A separate device description update is not necessary because this is made automatically by a firmware update.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The firmware or device description files do not match to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the files. Change them or change the device, if necesary.

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: This Message is thrown always, if the Device enters an error-free state.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An Axis entered the error free state.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Short circuit (motor-side)

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The drive hardware detected an over-current on the motor phases. The short circuit detection was triggered.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor cable.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor cable

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor winding.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor winding with an high voltage test or check the winding resistance.

CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor cable

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor winding.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor winding with an high voltage test or check the winding resistance.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Phase U current offset out of range

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The measured current offset of Phase U is outside the accepted range.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An unknown hard- or software error has occurred.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Disconnect the power supply module from the mains (including the 24 V power supply) and start a new attempt. If this error occurs repeatedly, please call the Beckhoff support that is responsible for you.

CauseRemedy.Remedy: Disconnect the power supply module from the mains (including the 24 V power supply) and start a new attempt. If this error occurs repeatedly, please call the Beckhoff support that is responsible for you.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The device might be influenced by an external magnetic field.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the environment of this device for magnetic components.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Phase failure motor

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The drive software detected an phase failure at the motor side. Please check wiring.

CauseRemedy.Cause: A power wire is not connected properly to the hybrid motor connector.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the power connections to the hybrid motor connector.

CauseRemedy.Cause: A power wire in the motor cable is broken.

Ch A, Primary Feedback: EnDat22: The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable, Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
Id=0x1: The 'operating status error sources' displays an multiturn error 1. Arg='OpStatErrSrc'
'OpStatErrSrc': Bit 0: LightSource Bit 1: SignalAmplitude Bit 2: SPos1 Bit 3: Overvoltage Bit 4: Undervoltage Bit 5: Overcurrent Bit 6: TemperatureExceeded Bit 7: SPos2 Bit 8: SSystem Bit 9: SAllPowerDown Bit 10: MPos1 : An M Pos 1 error message signals that the multiturn scanning or processing of the multiturn position has failed during encoder operation. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The consistency of the revolution counter value must be checked. If this is not possible, the axis must be referenced. Bit 11: MPos2 Bit 12: MSystem : An M System error message signals that a multiturn-related internal error during the initialization phase of the encoder has occurred. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The power-on cycle should be repeated. If this also fails, a hardware problem of the encoder is probable. The consistency of the revolution counter value must also be checked. Bit 13: MPowerFailure : The M Power failure error message signalizes that both the voltage of the buffer battery (UBAT) and the main supply voltage (UP) have fallen below the defined limit values. The subsequent electronics can only read out this error message when the main voltage supply has been restored. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not defined and therefore faulty. During the M Power failure state there is no revolution counting. The possibly simultaneously occurring error messages M Pos 1, M System and M Overflow are to be ignored. Corrective measure: The axis must be referenced again. Bit 14: MOverflow : The M Overflow error message signals that the specified (multiturn) counting range of the encoder has been exceeded. The encoder remains fully functional. M Overflow error messages can only be cleared when the multiturn value is again in the specified counting range. Corrective measure: Bring the axis into the specified counting range of the encoder again and clear error messages according to the EnDat specification. Bit 15: MBattery

Event.Message: Ch A, Primary Feedback: BiSS-C: Encoder error (position invalid), Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
The encoder could not transmit a valid position. Id=0x%01: Position status signals an error. Arg='Position Status'
'Position Status' Bit 0: ChannelEnable Bit 1: Error, Internal error occured, reported by ic-haus IPCore. Bit 2: PosReady, Position received and shifted, ready to be read by drive. Bit 3: EncReady, Set once the ic-haus IPCore has been set up and is running. No evaluation of encoder's answers or correctnes of configuration. Bit 4: LastPosValid, Position in last communication cycle was valid. Bit 5: PosValid, Combinated evaluation of Bits -Error (Bit 1 of this status) -nAGSError (Bit 9 of this status) -Position valid from ic-haus core (position received, CRC validated, Bit 12 of this status) -nSCDError (Bit 8 of this status) Bit 6: REGEND, Register Communication, not used Bit 7: nREGERR, Register Communication, not used Bit 8: nSCDERR , An error in the single cycle data detected by checksum verification (CRC) is shown with nSCDERR. If a sensor data error is signaled, the faulty sensor can be verified by reading SVALIDx. The nSCDERR flag is set after power on and after executing INIT. Bit 9: nAGSERR, An AGS watchdog error nAGSERR is set during the automatic transmission of sensor data enabled by the instruction bit AGS if no new cycle could be initiated. If the last BiSS frame has not been finished in time, the next BiSS frame will be omitted. The following BiSS frame will be executed if possible. The nAGSERR flag is set when resetting the instruction bit AGS (typically by writing BREAK into the instruction register. (We do not use AGS, but the signal is misbehaving sometimes) Bit 10: EOT, End Of Transmission, no encoder communication currently active Bit 11: SLO_line_state, Current Status of SL, directly measured at the line, no core required. Bit 12: SVALID1, The CRC verification result of the received single cycle sensor data of every BiSS frame is written to the validity message register SVALID for each slave separately. If the CRC is disabled in the slave configuration the correspondent SVALID flag is set after the reading of the sensor data is complete. After reading the sensor data, it is recommended to reset the validity flags by writing to the SVALID register. This way, it is possible to recognize updated sensor data. Bit 13: rsvd : 1; Bit 14: SenseData0, Bit 0 of received data, should be ENCODER WARNING in all BiSS-C encoders. Bit 15: SenseData1, Bit 1 of received data, should be ENCODER ERROR in all BiSS-C encoders.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Several causes, such as incorrect parameters or incorrect encoder connection to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check encoder status in the parameter list (Encoder actual values)

Detail.Text: 'FGerrCode' description: 0x0000 ERR_UNKNOWN The cause of the error is unknown; this code is used if the encoder cannot classify the error 0x0001 FGERR_RECONFIGURE Device is in configuration as a result of RECONFIGURE 0x0002 FGERR_ECHO An ECHO is being responded to 0x0100 FGERR_INVALID_FID An invalid FID was configured Correct the application 0x0101 FGERR_DUPLICATE_FID FID was selected more than once during the cycle 0x0200 FGERR_INVALID_DATA LPF is supported, but invalid data were delivered internally 0x0201 FGERR_INT_TRM LPF is supported but is currently not available (value could not be formed in time) 0x0300 FGERR_NO_SENSOR_DATA Sensor box data not available 0x1100 BGERR_USAGE Generic operator error 0x1101 BGERR_USAGE_OPCODE Operator error: invalid or unsupported command code 0x1102 BGERR_USAGE_ARGUMENTS Operator error: invalid arguments 0x1103 BGERR_USAGE_SEQUENCE Operator error: invalid command sequence 0x1104 BGERR_USAGE_ACCESS_DENIED Operator error: access denied; 0x1105 BGERR_USAGE_MEM_ADDRESS Operator error: access to invalid address 0x1106 BGERR_USAGE_NO_BG Encoder fundamentally does not support background processing 0x1200 BGERR_INTERNAL Generic exception error in the encoder 0x1201 BGERR_INTERNAL_MEMORY Exception error in encoder when accessing memory 0x1202 BGERR_INTERNAL_CONFIG Exception error in encoder: configuration invalid

Event.Message: Ch A, Primary Feedback: Inc Enc: Encoder error (position invalid), Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
The encoder could not transmit a valid position. Id=0x%01: Position status signals an error. Arg='Position Status'
'Position Status' Bit 0: ChannelEnable Bit 1: Error, Internal error occured, reported by ic-haus IPCore. Bit 2: PosReady, Position received and shifted, ready to be read by drive. Bit 3: EncReady, Set once the ic-haus IPCore has been set up and is running. No evaluation of encoder's answers or correctnes of configuration. Bit 4: LastPosValid, Position in last communication cycle was valid. Bit 5: PosValid , Combinated evaluation of Bits -Error (Bit 1 of this status) -nAGSError (Bit 9 of this status) -Position valid from ic-haus core (position received, CRC validated, Bit 12 of this status) -nSCDError (Bit 8 of this status) Bit 6: Bit 7: Bit 8: Bit 9: Bit 10: Bit 11: Bit 12: Bit 13: Bit 14: Bit 15:

CauseRemedy.Cause: Several causes, such as incorrect parameters or incorrect encoder connection to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check encoder status in the parameter list (Encoder actual values)

Detail.Text: There is no primary position offset stored, for the selected source 'drive memory'.

CauseRemedy.Cause: A position offset should used in the position control loop, but no position offset has been saved.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Calibrate the axis and save the new position offset.

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Offset additional position actual value: No position offset existing in source 'drive memory'

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: There is no secondary position offset stored, for the selected source 'drive memory'.

CauseRemedy.Cause: A position offset should used in the position control loop, but no position offset has been saved.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Calibrate the axis and save the new position offset.

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Jerk factor illegal. A possible Value would be {0}/{1}.

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The actual combination of the factor group Parameters is not allowed for this Device.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The jerk factor (Object 0x60A2 ChA or 0x68A2 ChB) does not adjust the velocity scaling to 100 degree/s^{2} in case of rotary Motors and 100 um/s^{2} in case of linear encoder.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please change your setting to the suggested value.

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: The range {0} of the Position range limit is below the minimum accepted value of {1}.

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The range of the Position range limit (Object 0x6096 ChA or 0x6896 ChB) is below the minimum accepted value. The Range is calculated 'max limit' - 'min limit' + 1 and has to be positive.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The range of the Position range limit (Object 0x6096 ChA or 0x6896 ChB) is below the minimum accepted value. The Range is calculated 'max limit' - 'min limit' + 1 and has to be positive.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the min and max value of the position range limit.

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Position range limit Inc with remainder is not supported for primary feedback.

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The position range limit is scaled internally to encoder increments. This calculation result contains a remainder, which is not supported for the primary feedback.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The position range limit is scaled internally to encoder increments. This calculation result contains a remainder, which is not supported for the primary feedback.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the position range limit and the factor group parameters of this feedback.

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Position range limit Inc with remainder is not supported for secondary feedback.

Detail.Name: Description

CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the position range limit and the factor group parameters of this feedback.

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Object 0x{0,X}/{1,X} changed in EtherCAT SafeOP or OP.

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: This errormessage was created, because this change during Runtime is potentially dangerous, if you don't know what you do.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The value of the position range limit or a Factor group object was changed in EtherCAT SafeOP or OP.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Execute fault reset command.

CauseRemedy.Cause: There is an internal hardware error.

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Axis fault reset command is not possible because at least one of the present errors cannot be reset.

CauseRemedy.Cause: This diagnostic message is just a hint that one of the present errors cannot be reset.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Rectify the present error.

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Autotuning command: Out of position range

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Permissible movement exceeded.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The system is unstable.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: May adjust the control loop parameters manually until the system behaves stable

CauseRemedy.Cause: The "Base velocity amplitude" is too high for the permissibled movement.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: May adjust "Base velocity amplitude" or the permissible movements.

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Advanced Tuning command: Excitation signal amplitude to high

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The current controller limitation is active during the excitation signal. So the excitation signal is not fully applied to the mech. system. This means that the measured frequency response is influenced by the current controllert limitation and so does not exactly represent the mechanical system behaviour.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The internal current controller output limitation is active
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Either, the excitation signal amplitude has to be reduced (additive excitation amplitude), or the drive has to be operated with a higher DC-link voltage

CauseRemedy.Cause: The modes of operation was set to an illegal value.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the value of Object 0x6060 (Ch A) or Object 0x6860 (Ch B).

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Error reaction "NC Handling" had a timeout

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: With NC error handling activated (Fault reaction option code), the Drive was not stopped by the NC within the parametrized time period (Error reaction delay time).

CauseRemedy.Cause: The selected time period is too short.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Increase the time period if your application allows this.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The movement is too complex for the parametrized time period.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Program a movement that is suitable for the time period.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The NC doesn't support this kind of error handling.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Ask support on which version the feature is supported.

Ch B, Primary Feedback: EnDat22: The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable, Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
Id=0x1: The 'operating status error sources' displays an multiturn error 1. Arg='OpStatErrSrc'
'OpStatErrSrc': Bit 0: LightSource Bit 1: SignalAmplitude Bit 2: SPos1 Bit 3: Overvoltage Bit 4: Undervoltage Bit 5: Overcurrent Bit 6: TemperatureExceeded Bit 7: SPos2 Bit 8: SSystem Bit 9: SAllPowerDown Bit 10: MPos1 : An M Pos 1 error message signals that the multiturn scanning or processing of the multiturn position has failed during encoder operation. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The consistency of the revolution counter value must be checked. If this is not possible, the axis must be referenced. Bit 11: MPos2 Bit 12: MSystem : An M System error message signals that a multiturn-related internal error during the initialization phase of the encoder has occurred. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The power-on cycle should be repeated. If this also fails, a hardware problem of the encoder is probable. The consistency of the revolution counter value must also be checked. Bit 13: MPowerFailure : The M Power failure error message signalizes that both the voltage of the buffer battery (UBAT) and the main supply voltage (UP) have fallen below the defined limit values. The subsequent electronics can only read out this error message when the main voltage supply has been restored. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not defined and therefore faulty. During the M Power failure state there is no revolution counting. The possibly simultaneously occurring error messages M Pos 1, M System and M Overflow are to be ignored. Corrective measure: The axis must be referenced again. Bit 14: MOverflow : The M Overflow error message signals that the specified (multiturn) counting range of the encoder has been exceeded. The encoder remains fully functional. M Overflow error messages can only be cleared when the multiturn value is again in the specified counting range. Corrective measure: Bring the axis into the specified counting range of the encoder again and clear error messages according to the EnDat specification. Bit 15: MBattery

Event.Message: Ch B, Primary Feedback: BiSS-C: Encoder error (position invalid), Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
The encoder could not transmit a valid position. Id=0x%01: Position status signals an error. Arg='Position Status'
'Position Status' Bit 0: ChannelEnable Bit 1: Error, Internal error occured, reported by ic-haus IPCore. Bit 2: PosReady, Position received and shifted, ready to be read by drive. Bit 3: EncReady, Set once the ic-haus IPCore has been set up and is running. No evaluation of encoder's answers or correctnes of configuration. Bit 4: LastPosValid, Position in last communication cycle was valid. Bit 5: PosValid, Combinated evaluation of Bits -Error (Bit 1 of this status) -nAGSError (Bit 9 of this status) -Position valid from ic-haus core (position received, CRC validated, Bit 12 of this status) -nSCDError (Bit 8 of this status) Bit 6: REGEND, Register Communication, not used Bit 7: nREGERR, Register Communication, not used Bit 8: nSCDERR , An error in the single cycle data detected by checksum verification (CRC) is shown with nSCDERR. If a sensor data error is signaled, the faulty sensor can be verified by reading SVALIDx. The nSCDERR flag is set after power on and after executing INIT. Bit 9: nAGSERR, An AGS watchdog error nAGSERR is set during the automatic transmission of sensor data enabled by the instruction bit AGS if no new cycle could be initiated. If the last BiSS frame has not been finished in time, the next BiSS frame will be omitted. The following BiSS frame will be executed if possible. The nAGSERR flag is set when resetting the instruction bit AGS (typically by writing BREAK into the instruction register. (We do not use AGS, but the signal is misbehaving sometimes) Bit 10: EOT, End Of Transmission, no encoder communication currently active Bit 11: SLO_line_state, Current Status of SL, directly measured at the line, no core required. Bit 12: SVALID1, The CRC verification result of the received single cycle sensor data of every BiSS frame is written to the validity message register SVALID for each slave separately. If the CRC is disabled in the slave configuration the correspondent SVALID flag is set after the reading of the sensor data is complete. After reading the sensor data, it is recommended to reset the validity flags by writing to the SVALID register. This way, it is possible to recognize updated sensor data. Bit 13: rsvd : 1; Bit 14: SenseData0, Bit 0 of received data, should be ENCODER WARNING in all BiSS-C encoders. Bit 15: SenseData1, Bit 1 of received data, should be ENCODER ERROR in all BiSS-C encoders.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Several causes, such as incorrect parameters or incorrect encoder connection to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check encoder status in the parameter list (Encoder actual values)

Ch A, AxisMainSlot: No Error

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: This Message is thrown always, if the Device enters an error-free state.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An Axis entered the error free state.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Short circuit (motor-side)

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The drive hardware detected an over-current on the motor phases. The short circuit detection was triggered.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor cable.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor cable

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor winding.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor winding with an high voltage test or check the winding resistance.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Continuous over current (device output side) Phase U

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The drive software detected an overcurrent on the motor phases U.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor cable.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor cable

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor winding.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor winding with an high voltage test or check the winding resistance.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Continuous over current (device output side) Phase V

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The drive software detected an overcurrent on the motor phases V.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor cable.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor cable

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor winding.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor winding with an high voltage test or check the winding resistance.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Continuous over current (device output side) Phase W

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The drive software detected an overcurrent on the motor phases W.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor cable.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor cable

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor winding.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor winding with an high voltage test or check the winding resistance.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Phase U current offset out of range

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The measured current offset of Phase U is outside the accepted range.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An unknown hard- or software error has occurred.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Disconnect the power supply module from the mains (including the 24 V power supply) and start a new attempt. If this error occurs repeatedly, please call the Beckhoff support that is responsible for you.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Phase V current offset out of range

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The measured current offset of Phase V is outside the accepted range.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An unknown hard- or software error has occurred.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Disconnect the power supply module from the mains (including the 24 V power supply) and start a new attempt. If this error occurs repeatedly, please call the Beckhoff support that is responsible for you.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Phase W current offset out of range

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The measured current offset of Phase W is outside the accepted range.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An unknown hard- or software error has occurred.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Disconnect the power supply module from the mains (including the 24 V power supply) and start a new attempt. If this error occurs repeatedly, please call the Beckhoff support that is responsible for you.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Motor brake current offset out of range

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The measured current offset of the motor brake is outside the accepted range.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An unknown hard- or software error has occurred.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Disconnect the power supply module from the mains (including the 24 V power supply) and start a new attempt. If this error occurs repeatedly, please call the Beckhoff support that is responsible for you.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The device might be influenced by an external magnetic field.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the environment of this device for magnetic components.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Phase failure motor

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The drive software detected an phase failure at the motor side. Please check wiring.

CauseRemedy.Cause: A power wire is not connected properly to the hybrid motor connector.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the power connections to the hybrid motor connector.

CauseRemedy.Cause: A power wire in the motor cable is broken.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the power wires in the motor cable.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The hybrid motor connector seems not to be plugged in properly.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check if the hybrid motor connector is plugged in properly.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: DC link under-voltage

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: An under-voltage occurred in the DC link circuit.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The DC link voltage level was under the configured minimum.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the minimum DC link voltage parameter. (Object 0x2C02/1)

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: DC link is not ready

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Axis got an enable command before DC link was ready.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your power supply device.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Drive overtemperature shut down

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The drive temperature has reached a critical value.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The ambient temperature is too high
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Cool down the ambient temperature

CauseRemedy.Cause: Internal brake power and power loss of axis are too high
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Lower the brake power and power loss of axis

CauseRemedy.Cause: The fan is defective
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the fan

CauseRemedy.Cause: The cooling slots or the measuring sensors are polluted
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Clean the cooling slots and the measuring sensors

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Output stage STO active.

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The Axis is unable to operate, because the Amplifier is locked from the safety module. (Safe Torque Off / STO)

CauseRemedy.Cause: The amplifier is locked by the safety module.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the status of the safety module.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Supply DC link circuit is not ready

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Power supply device is not ready.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please Check the Messages and the Status of the Supply Device.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Power supply communication is not established

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Power supply status is not alive.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please Check if the Power supply controlword of this Axis Device is linked to the Power Supply Device and the Device is in EtherCAT OP.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Power supply SDO communications are not finished.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please Check if the Power supply communication parameters and status of DeviceMain.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Positive limit switch active

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Positive limit switch reached

CauseRemedy.Cause: The axis has been moved to the positive limit switch.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please move the axis away from the positive limit switch.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Negative limit switch active

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Negative limit switch reached

CauseRemedy.Cause: The axis has been moved to the negative limit switch.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please move the axis away from the negative limit switch.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Loss of the hardware enable

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The configured hardware enable input has been deactivated by an external event, even though the AX8000 was under control.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Problems with the digital inputs
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the digital inputs

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Loss of the hardware enable (Reaction TorqueOff)

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The configured hardware enable input has been deactivated by an external event, even though the AX8000 was under control.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Problems with the digital inputs
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the digital inputs

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Fast stop switch active

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Positive limit switch reached

CauseRemedy.Cause: The fast stop switch has been activated.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please move the axis away from the fast stop switch.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Positive limit switch active

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Positive limit switch reached

CauseRemedy.Cause: The axis has been moved to the positive limit switch.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please move the axis away from the positive limit switch.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Negative limit switch active

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Negative limit switch reached

CauseRemedy.Cause: The axis has been moved to the negative limit switch.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please move the axis away from the negative limit switch.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Fast stop switch active

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Positive limit switch reached

CauseRemedy.Cause: The fast stop switch has been activated.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please move the axis away from the fast stop switch.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: The Axis seems not to be parameterized.

CauseRemedy.Remedy: Write your drive type into 'AxisMain parameters/Configured drive type'.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Factor Group Parameters: Feed constant illegal feed

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The actual combination of the factor group Parameters is not allowed for this Device.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The feed constant - feed contains an illegal value (Object 0x6092/1 ChA or 0x6892/1 ChB).
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please use a 2^{x} value (x from 16 to 28) for rotary encoders and a 10^{x} value (x from 0 to 9) for linear encoders.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Factor Group Parameters: Feed constant illegal shaft revolutions

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The actual combination of the factor group Parameters is not allowed for this Device.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The feed constant - shaft revolutions contains an illegal value (Object 0x6092/2 ChA or 0x6892/2 ChB).
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please set value to '1'.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Factor Group Parameters: Gear ratio illegal Motor shaft revolutions

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The actual combination of the factor group Parameters is not allowed for this Device.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The gear ratio - motor shaft revolutions contains an illegal value (Object 0x6091/1 ChA or 0x6891/1 ChB).
CauseRemedy.Remedy: You might add the default value here.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Factor Group Parameters: Position encoder resolution illegal encoder increments

Detail.Name: Description

CauseRemedy.Cause: The position encoder resolution - encoder increments contains an illegal value (Object 0x608F/1 ChA or 0x688F/1 ChB).
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please compare it to your encoder values.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Advanced Tuning command: Excitation signal amplitude to high

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The current controller limitation is active during the excitation signal. So the excitation signal is not fully applied to the mech. system. This means that the measured frequency response is influenced by the current controllert limitation and so does not exactly represent the mechanical system behaviour.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The internal current controller output limitation is active
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Either, the excitation signal amplitude has to be reduced (additive excitation amplitude), or the drive has to be operated with a higher DC-link voltage

Ch A, Primary Feedback: EnDat22: The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable, Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
Id=0x1: The 'operating status error sources' displays an multiturn error 1. Arg='OpStatErrSrc'
'OpStatErrSrc': Bit 0: LightSource Bit 1: SignalAmplitude Bit 2: SPos1 Bit 3: Overvoltage Bit 4: Undervoltage Bit 5: Overcurrent Bit 6: TemperatureExceeded Bit 7: SPos2 Bit 8: SSystem Bit 9: SAllPowerDown Bit 10: MPos1 : An M Pos 1 error message signals that the multiturn scanning or processing of the multiturn position has failed during encoder operation. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The consistency of the revolution counter value must be checked. If this is not possible, the axis must be referenced. Bit 11: MPos2 Bit 12: MSystem : An M System error message signals that a multiturn-related internal error during the initialization phase of the encoder has occurred. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The power-on cycle should be repeated. If this also fails, a hardware problem of the encoder is probable. The consistency of the revolution counter value must also be checked. Bit 13: MPowerFailure : The M Power failure error message signalizes that both the voltage of the buffer battery (UBAT) and the main supply voltage (UP) have fallen below the defined limit values. The subsequent electronics can only read out this error message when the main voltage supply has been restored. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not defined and therefore faulty. During the M Power failure state there is no revolution counting. The possibly simultaneously occurring error messages M Pos 1, M System and M Overflow are to be ignored. Corrective measure: The axis must be referenced again. Bit 14: MOverflow : The M Overflow error message signals that the specified (multiturn) counting range of the encoder has been exceeded. The encoder remains fully functional. M Overflow error messages can only be cleared when the multiturn value is again in the specified counting range. Corrective measure: Bring the axis into the specified counting range of the encoder again and clear error messages according to the EnDat specification. Bit 15: MBattery

Event.Message: Ch A, Primary Feedback: BiSS-C: Encoder error (position invalid), Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
The encoder could not transmit a valid position. Id=0x%01: Position status signals an error. Arg='Position Status'
'Position Status' Bit 0: ChannelEnable Bit 1: Error, Internal error occured, reported by ic-haus IPCore. Bit 2: PosReady, Position received and shifted, ready to be read by drive. Bit 3: EncReady, Set once the ic-haus IPCore has been set up and is running. No evaluation of encoder's answers or correctnes of configuration. Bit 4: LastPosValid, Position in last communication cycle was valid. Bit 5: PosValid, Combinated evaluation of Bits -Error (Bit 1 of this status) -nAGSError (Bit 9 of this status) -Position valid from ic-haus core (position received, CRC validated, Bit 12 of this status) -nSCDError (Bit 8 of this status) Bit 6: REGEND, Register Communication, not used Bit 7: nREGERR, Register Communication, not used Bit 8: nSCDERR , An error in the single cycle data detected by checksum verification (CRC) is shown with nSCDERR. If a sensor data error is signaled, the faulty sensor can be verified by reading SVALIDx. The nSCDERR flag is set after power on and after executing INIT. Bit 9: nAGSERR, An AGS watchdog error nAGSERR is set during the automatic transmission of sensor data enabled by the instruction bit AGS if no new cycle could be initiated. If the last BiSS frame has not been finished in time, the next BiSS frame will be omitted. The following BiSS frame will be executed if possible. The nAGSERR flag is set when resetting the instruction bit AGS (typically by writing BREAK into the instruction register. (We do not use AGS, but the signal is misbehaving sometimes) Bit 10: EOT, End Of Transmission, no encoder communication currently active Bit 11: SLO_line_state, Current Status of SL, directly measured at the line, no core required. Bit 12: SVALID1, The CRC verification result of the received single cycle sensor data of every BiSS frame is written to the validity message register SVALID for each slave separately. If the CRC is disabled in the slave configuration the correspondent SVALID flag is set after the reading of the sensor data is complete. After reading the sensor data, it is recommended to reset the validity flags by writing to the SVALID register. This way, it is possible to recognize updated sensor data. Bit 13: rsvd : 1; Bit 14: SenseData0, Bit 0 of received data, should be ENCODER WARNING in all BiSS-C encoders. Bit 15: SenseData1, Bit 1 of received data, should be ENCODER ERROR in all BiSS-C encoders.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Several causes, such as incorrect parameters or incorrect encoder connection to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check encoder status in the parameter list (Encoder actual values)

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Advanced Tuning command: Excitation signal amplitude to high

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The current controller limitation is active during the excitation signal. So the excitation signal is not fully applied to the mech. system. This means that the measured frequency response is influenced by the current controllert limitation and so does not exactly represent the mechanical system behaviour.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The internal current controller output limitation is active
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Either, the excitation signal amplitude has to be reduced (additive excitation amplitude), or the drive has to be operated with a higher DC-link voltage

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Error reaction "NC Handling" had a timeout

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: With NC error handling activated (Fault reaction option code), the Drive was not stopped by the NC within the parametrized time period (Error reaction delay time).

CauseRemedy.Cause: The selected time period is too short.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Increase the time period if your application allows this.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The movement is too complex for the parametrized time period.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Program a movement that is suitable for the time period.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The NC doesn't support this kind of error handling.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Ask support on which version the feature is supported.

Event.Message: Ch B, Primary Feedback: HpfDsl: Encoder error (position invalid), Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
The encoder position is invalid:
Id=1: Got no valid position from the HpfDsl-Ip-Core. Arg = 'Internal status word' Id=2: The position extrapolator error limit is reached. Arg = 'Internal status word' Id=3: The position extrapolator is too many cycles active. Arg = value of the cycle counter
'Internal status word': Bit 0: Enabled : IpCore enable Bit 1: rsvd0 Bit 2: PosReady : Position ready to use Bit 3: StartupDone : Internal startup done Bit 4: PosErrorLimitExceeded : Extrapolator position limit exceeded Bit 5: rsvd1 Bit 6: InterruptCorePin Bit 7: SyncD : IpCore is synced. Bit 8: PRST Bit 9: QMLW Bit 10: VPOSerror Bit 11: POSerror Bit 12: LastPosValid : Position from the previous cycle is valid. Bit 13: VRTerror Bit 14: SUM Bit 15: InterruptOnlineStatus

Ch B, Primary Feedback: EnDat22: The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable, Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
Id=0x1: The 'operating status error sources' displays an multiturn error 1. Arg='OpStatErrSrc'
'OpStatErrSrc': Bit 0: LightSource Bit 1: SignalAmplitude Bit 2: SPos1 Bit 3: Overvoltage Bit 4: Undervoltage Bit 5: Overcurrent Bit 6: TemperatureExceeded Bit 7: SPos2 Bit 8: SSystem Bit 9: SAllPowerDown Bit 10: MPos1 : An M Pos 1 error message signals that the multiturn scanning or processing of the multiturn position has failed during encoder operation. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The consistency of the revolution counter value must be checked. If this is not possible, the axis must be referenced. Bit 11: MPos2 Bit 12: MSystem : An M System error message signals that a multiturn-related internal error during the initialization phase of the encoder has occurred. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The power-on cycle should be repeated. If this also fails, a hardware problem of the encoder is probable. The consistency of the revolution counter value must also be checked. Bit 13: MPowerFailure : The M Power failure error message signalizes that both the voltage of the buffer battery (UBAT) and the main supply voltage (UP) have fallen below the defined limit values. The subsequent electronics can only read out this error message when the main voltage supply has been restored. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not defined and therefore faulty. During the M Power failure state there is no revolution counting. The possibly simultaneously occurring error messages M Pos 1, M System and M Overflow are to be ignored. Corrective measure: The axis must be referenced again. Bit 14: MOverflow : The M Overflow error message signals that the specified (multiturn) counting range of the encoder has been exceeded. The encoder remains fully functional. M Overflow error messages can only be cleared when the multiturn value is again in the specified counting range. Corrective measure: Bring the axis into the specified counting range of the encoder again and clear error messages according to the EnDat specification. Bit 15: MBattery

Event.Message: Ch B, Primary Feedback: BiSS-C: Encoder error (position invalid), Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
The encoder could not transmit a valid position. Id=0x%01: Position status signals an error. Arg='Position Status'
'Position Status' Bit 0: ChannelEnable Bit 1: Error, Internal error occured, reported by ic-haus IPCore. Bit 2: PosReady, Position received and shifted, ready to be read by drive. Bit 3: EncReady, Set once the ic-haus IPCore has been set up and is running. No evaluation of encoder's answers or correctnes of configuration. Bit 4: LastPosValid, Position in last communication cycle was valid. Bit 5: PosValid, Combinated evaluation of Bits -Error (Bit 1 of this status) -nAGSError (Bit 9 of this status) -Position valid from ic-haus core (position received, CRC validated, Bit 12 of this status) -nSCDError (Bit 8 of this status) Bit 6: REGEND, Register Communication, not used Bit 7: nREGERR, Register Communication, not used Bit 8: nSCDERR , An error in the single cycle data detected by checksum verification (CRC) is shown with nSCDERR. If a sensor data error is signaled, the faulty sensor can be verified by reading SVALIDx. The nSCDERR flag is set after power on and after executing INIT. Bit 9: nAGSERR, An AGS watchdog error nAGSERR is set during the automatic transmission of sensor data enabled by the instruction bit AGS if no new cycle could be initiated. If the last BiSS frame has not been finished in time, the next BiSS frame will be omitted. The following BiSS frame will be executed if possible. The nAGSERR flag is set when resetting the instruction bit AGS (typically by writing BREAK into the instruction register. (We do not use AGS, but the signal is misbehaving sometimes) Bit 10: EOT, End Of Transmission, no encoder communication currently active Bit 11: SLO_line_state, Current Status of SL, directly measured at the line, no core required. Bit 12: SVALID1, The CRC verification result of the received single cycle sensor data of every BiSS frame is written to the validity message register SVALID for each slave separately. If the CRC is disabled in the slave configuration the correspondent SVALID flag is set after the reading of the sensor data is complete. After reading the sensor data, it is recommended to reset the validity flags by writing to the SVALID register. This way, it is possible to recognize updated sensor data. Bit 13: rsvd : 1; Bit 14: SenseData0, Bit 0 of received data, should be ENCODER WARNING in all BiSS-C encoders. Bit 15: SenseData1, Bit 1 of received data, should be ENCODER ERROR in all BiSS-C encoders.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Several causes, such as incorrect parameters or incorrect encoder connection to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check encoder status in the parameter list (Encoder actual values)

Event.Message: Ch B, Primary Feedback: Inc Enc: Encoder error (position invalid), Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
The encoder could not transmit a valid position. Id=0x%01: Position status signals an error. Arg='Position Status'
'Position Status' Bit 0: ChannelEnable Bit 1: Error, Internal error occured, reported by ic-haus IPCore. Bit 2: PosReady, Position received and shifted, ready to be read by drive. Bit 3: EncReady, Set once the ic-haus IPCore has been set up and is running. No evaluation of encoder's answers or correctnes of configuration. Bit 4: LastPosValid, Position in last communication cycle was valid. Bit 5: PosValid , Combinated evaluation of Bits -Error (Bit 1 of this status) -nAGSError (Bit 9 of this status) -Position valid from ic-haus core (position received, CRC validated, Bit 12 of this status) -nSCDError (Bit 8 of this status) Bit 6: Bit 7: Bit 8: Bit 9: Bit 10: Bit 11: Bit 12: Bit 13: Bit 14: Bit 15:

CauseRemedy.Cause: Several causes, such as incorrect parameters or incorrect encoder connection to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check encoder status in the parameter list (Encoder actual values)

Ch A, AxisMainSlot: No Error

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: This Message is thrown always, if the Device enters an error-free state.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An Axis entered the error free state.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Short circuit (motor-side)

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The drive hardware detected an over-current on the motor phases. The short circuit detection was triggered.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor cable.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor cable

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor winding.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor winding with an high voltage test or check the winding resistance.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Phase U current offset out of range

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The measured current offset of Phase U is outside the accepted range.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An unknown hard- or software error has occurred.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Disconnect the power supply module from the mains (including the 24 V power supply) and start a new attempt. If this error occurs repeatedly, please call the Beckhoff support that is responsible for you.

CauseRemedy.Remedy: Disconnect the power supply module from the mains (including the 24 V power supply) and start a new attempt. If this error occurs repeatedly, please call the Beckhoff support that is responsible for you.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The device might be influenced by an external magnetic field.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the environment of this device for magnetic components.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Phase failure motor

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The drive software detected an phase failure at the motor side. Please check wiring.

CauseRemedy.Cause: A power wire is not connected properly to the hybrid motor connector.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the power connections to the hybrid motor connector.

CauseRemedy.Cause: A power wire in the motor cable is broken.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the power wires in the motor cable.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The hybrid motor connector seems not to be plugged in properly.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check if the hybrid motor connector is plugged in properly.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: DC link under-voltage

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: An under-voltage occurred in the DC link circuit.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The DC link voltage level was under the configured minimum.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the minimum DC link voltage parameter. (Object 0x2C02/1)

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: DC link is not ready

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Axis got an enable command before DC link was ready.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your power supply device.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Drive overtemperature shut down

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The drive temperature has reached a critical value.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The ambient temperature is too high
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Cool down the ambient temperature

CauseRemedy.Cause: Internal brake power and power loss of axis are too high
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Lower the brake power and power loss of axis

CauseRemedy.Cause: The fan is defective
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the fan

CauseRemedy.Cause: The cooling slots or the measuring sensors are polluted
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Clean the cooling slots and the measuring sensors

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Output stage STO active.

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The Axis is unable to operate, because the Amplifier is locked from the safety module. (Safe Torque Off / STO)

CauseRemedy.Cause: The amplifier is locked by the safety module.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the status of the safety module.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Supply DC link circuit is not ready

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Power supply device is not ready.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please Check the Messages and the Status of the Supply Device.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Power supply communication is not established

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Power supply status is not alive.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please Check if the Power supply controlword of this Axis Device is linked to the Power Supply Device and the Device is in EtherCAT OP.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Power supply SDO communications are not finished.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please Check if the Power supply communication parameters and status of DeviceMain.

Event.Message: Ch A, AxisMainSlot: Advanced Tuning command: Excitation signal amplitude to high

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The current controller limitation is active during the excitation signal. So the excitation signal is not fully applied to the mech. system. This means that the measured frequency response is influenced by the current controllert limitation and so does not exactly represent the mechanical system behaviour.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The internal current controller output limitation is active
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Either, the excitation signal amplitude has to be reduced (additive excitation amplitude), or the drive has to be operated with a higher DC-link voltage

Ch A, Primary Feedback: EnDat22: The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable, Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
Id=0x1: The 'operating status error sources' displays an multiturn error 1. Arg='OpStatErrSrc'
'OpStatErrSrc': Bit 0: LightSource Bit 1: SignalAmplitude Bit 2: SPos1 Bit 3: Overvoltage Bit 4: Undervoltage Bit 5: Overcurrent Bit 6: TemperatureExceeded Bit 7: SPos2 Bit 8: SSystem Bit 9: SAllPowerDown Bit 10: MPos1 : An M Pos 1 error message signals that the multiturn scanning or processing of the multiturn position has failed during encoder operation. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The consistency of the revolution counter value must be checked. If this is not possible, the axis must be referenced. Bit 11: MPos2 Bit 12: MSystem : An M System error message signals that a multiturn-related internal error during the initialization phase of the encoder has occurred. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The power-on cycle should be repeated. If this also fails, a hardware problem of the encoder is probable. The consistency of the revolution counter value must also be checked. Bit 13: MPowerFailure : The M Power failure error message signalizes that both the voltage of the buffer battery (UBAT) and the main supply voltage (UP) have fallen below the defined limit values. The subsequent electronics can only read out this error message when the main voltage supply has been restored. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not defined and therefore faulty. During the M Power failure state there is no revolution counting. The possibly simultaneously occurring error messages M Pos 1, M System and M Overflow are to be ignored. Corrective measure: The axis must be referenced again. Bit 14: MOverflow : The M Overflow error message signals that the specified (multiturn) counting range of the encoder has been exceeded. The encoder remains fully functional. M Overflow error messages can only be cleared when the multiturn value is again in the specified counting range. Corrective measure: Bring the axis into the specified counting range of the encoder again and clear error messages according to the EnDat specification. Bit 15: MBattery

Event.Message: Ch A, Primary Feedback: BiSS-C: Encoder error (position invalid), Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
The encoder could not transmit a valid position. Id=0x%01: Position status signals an error. Arg='Position Status'
'Position Status' Bit 0: ChannelEnable Bit 1: Error, Internal error occured, reported by ic-haus IPCore. Bit 2: PosReady, Position received and shifted, ready to be read by drive. Bit 3: EncReady, Set once the ic-haus IPCore has been set up and is running. No evaluation of encoder's answers or correctnes of configuration. Bit 4: LastPosValid, Position in last communication cycle was valid. Bit 5: PosValid, Combinated evaluation of Bits -Error (Bit 1 of this status) -nAGSError (Bit 9 of this status) -Position valid from ic-haus core (position received, CRC validated, Bit 12 of this status) -nSCDError (Bit 8 of this status) Bit 6: REGEND, Register Communication, not used Bit 7: nREGERR, Register Communication, not used Bit 8: nSCDERR , An error in the single cycle data detected by checksum verification (CRC) is shown with nSCDERR. If a sensor data error is signaled, the faulty sensor can be verified by reading SVALIDx. The nSCDERR flag is set after power on and after executing INIT. Bit 9: nAGSERR, An AGS watchdog error nAGSERR is set during the automatic transmission of sensor data enabled by the instruction bit AGS if no new cycle could be initiated. If the last BiSS frame has not been finished in time, the next BiSS frame will be omitted. The following BiSS frame will be executed if possible. The nAGSERR flag is set when resetting the instruction bit AGS (typically by writing BREAK into the instruction register. (We do not use AGS, but the signal is misbehaving sometimes) Bit 10: EOT, End Of Transmission, no encoder communication currently active Bit 11: SLO_line_state, Current Status of SL, directly measured at the line, no core required. Bit 12: SVALID1, The CRC verification result of the received single cycle sensor data of every BiSS frame is written to the validity message register SVALID for each slave separately. If the CRC is disabled in the slave configuration the correspondent SVALID flag is set after the reading of the sensor data is complete. After reading the sensor data, it is recommended to reset the validity flags by writing to the SVALID register. This way, it is possible to recognize updated sensor data. Bit 13: rsvd : 1; Bit 14: SenseData0, Bit 0 of received data, should be ENCODER WARNING in all BiSS-C encoders. Bit 15: SenseData1, Bit 1 of received data, should be ENCODER ERROR in all BiSS-C encoders.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Several causes, such as incorrect parameters or incorrect encoder connection to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check encoder status in the parameter list (Encoder actual values)

Event.Message: Ch A, Primary Feedback: Inc Enc: Encoder error (position invalid), Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
The encoder could not transmit a valid position. Id=0x%01: Position status signals an error. Arg='Position Status'
'Position Status' Bit 0: ChannelEnable Bit 1: Error, Internal error occured, reported by ic-haus IPCore. Bit 2: PosReady, Position received and shifted, ready to be read by drive. Bit 3: EncReady, Set once the ic-haus IPCore has been set up and is running. No evaluation of encoder's answers or correctnes of configuration. Bit 4: LastPosValid, Position in last communication cycle was valid. Bit 5: PosValid , Combinated evaluation of Bits -Error (Bit 1 of this status) -nAGSError (Bit 9 of this status) -Position valid from ic-haus core (position received, CRC validated, Bit 12 of this status) -nSCDError (Bit 8 of this status) Bit 6: Bit 7: Bit 8: Bit 9: Bit 10: Bit 11: Bit 12: Bit 13: Bit 14: Bit 15:

CauseRemedy.Cause: Several causes, such as incorrect parameters or incorrect encoder connection to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check encoder status in the parameter list (Encoder actual values)

CauseRemedy.Cause: There is an internal hardware error.

CauseRemedy.Cause: This diagnostic message is just a hint that one of the present errors cannot be reset.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Rectify the present error.

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Autotuning command: Out of position range

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: Permissible movement exceeded.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The system is unstable.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: May adjust the control loop parameters manually until the system behaves stable

CauseRemedy.Cause: The "Base velocity amplitude" is too high for the permissibled movement.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: May adjust "Base velocity amplitude" or the permissible movements.

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Advanced Tuning command: Excitation signal amplitude to high

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: The current controller limitation is active during the excitation signal. So the excitation signal is not fully applied to the mech. system. This means that the measured frequency response is influenced by the current controllert limitation and so does not exactly represent the mechanical system behaviour.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The internal current controller output limitation is active
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Either, the excitation signal amplitude has to be reduced (additive excitation amplitude), or the drive has to be operated with a higher DC-link voltage

Event.Message: Ch B, AxisMainSlot: Error reaction "NC Handling" had a timeout

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text: With NC error handling activated (Fault reaction option code), the Drive was not stopped by the NC within the parametrized time period (Error reaction delay time).

CauseRemedy.Cause: The selected time period is too short.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Increase the time period if your application allows this.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The movement is too complex for the parametrized time period.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Program a movement that is suitable for the time period.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The NC doesn't support this kind of error handling.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Ask support on which version the feature is supported.

Ch B, Primary Feedback: EnDat22: The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable, Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
Id=0x1: The 'operating status error sources' displays an multiturn error 1. Arg='OpStatErrSrc'
'OpStatErrSrc': Bit 0: LightSource Bit 1: SignalAmplitude Bit 2: SPos1 Bit 3: Overvoltage Bit 4: Undervoltage Bit 5: Overcurrent Bit 6: TemperatureExceeded Bit 7: SPos2 Bit 8: SSystem Bit 9: SAllPowerDown Bit 10: MPos1 : An M Pos 1 error message signals that the multiturn scanning or processing of the multiturn position has failed during encoder operation. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The consistency of the revolution counter value must be checked. If this is not possible, the axis must be referenced. Bit 11: MPos2 Bit 12: MSystem : An M System error message signals that a multiturn-related internal error during the initialization phase of the encoder has occurred. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not reliable under these conditions. Corrective measure: The power-on cycle should be repeated. If this also fails, a hardware problem of the encoder is probable. The consistency of the revolution counter value must also be checked. Bit 13: MPowerFailure : The M Power failure error message signalizes that both the voltage of the buffer battery (UBAT) and the main supply voltage (UP) have fallen below the defined limit values. The subsequent electronics can only read out this error message when the main voltage supply has been restored. The multiturn part of the transferred position value is not defined and therefore faulty. During the M Power failure state there is no revolution counting. The possibly simultaneously occurring error messages M Pos 1, M System and M Overflow are to be ignored. Corrective measure: The axis must be referenced again. Bit 14: MOverflow : The M Overflow error message signals that the specified (multiturn) counting range of the encoder has been exceeded. The encoder remains fully functional. M Overflow error messages can only be cleared when the multiturn value is again in the specified counting range. Corrective measure: Bring the axis into the specified counting range of the encoder again and clear error messages according to the EnDat specification. Bit 15: MBattery

Event.Message: Ch B, Primary Feedback: BiSS-C: Encoder error (position invalid), Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
The encoder could not transmit a valid position. Id=0x%01: Position status signals an error. Arg='Position Status'
'Position Status' Bit 0: ChannelEnable Bit 1: Error, Internal error occured, reported by ic-haus IPCore. Bit 2: PosReady, Position received and shifted, ready to be read by drive. Bit 3: EncReady, Set once the ic-haus IPCore has been set up and is running. No evaluation of encoder's answers or correctnes of configuration. Bit 4: LastPosValid, Position in last communication cycle was valid. Bit 5: PosValid, Combinated evaluation of Bits -Error (Bit 1 of this status) -nAGSError (Bit 9 of this status) -Position valid from ic-haus core (position received, CRC validated, Bit 12 of this status) -nSCDError (Bit 8 of this status) Bit 6: REGEND, Register Communication, not used Bit 7: nREGERR, Register Communication, not used Bit 8: nSCDERR , An error in the single cycle data detected by checksum verification (CRC) is shown with nSCDERR. If a sensor data error is signaled, the faulty sensor can be verified by reading SVALIDx. The nSCDERR flag is set after power on and after executing INIT. Bit 9: nAGSERR, An AGS watchdog error nAGSERR is set during the automatic transmission of sensor data enabled by the instruction bit AGS if no new cycle could be initiated. If the last BiSS frame has not been finished in time, the next BiSS frame will be omitted. The following BiSS frame will be executed if possible. The nAGSERR flag is set when resetting the instruction bit AGS (typically by writing BREAK into the instruction register. (We do not use AGS, but the signal is misbehaving sometimes) Bit 10: EOT, End Of Transmission, no encoder communication currently active Bit 11: SLO_line_state, Current Status of SL, directly measured at the line, no core required. Bit 12: SVALID1, The CRC verification result of the received single cycle sensor data of every BiSS frame is written to the validity message register SVALID for each slave separately. If the CRC is disabled in the slave configuration the correspondent SVALID flag is set after the reading of the sensor data is complete. After reading the sensor data, it is recommended to reset the validity flags by writing to the SVALID register. This way, it is possible to recognize updated sensor data. Bit 13: rsvd : 1; Bit 14: SenseData0, Bit 0 of received data, should be ENCODER WARNING in all BiSS-C encoders. Bit 15: SenseData1, Bit 1 of received data, should be ENCODER ERROR in all BiSS-C encoders.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Several causes, such as incorrect parameters or incorrect encoder connection to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check encoder status in the parameter list (Encoder actual values)

Event.Message: Ch B, Primary Feedback: Inc Enc: Encoder error (position invalid), Id=0x{0,X}, Arg=0x{1,X}

Detail.Name: Description
Detail.Text:
The encoder could not transmit a valid position. Id=0x%01: Position status signals an error. Arg='Position Status'
'Position Status' Bit 0: ChannelEnable Bit 1: Error, Internal error occured, reported by ic-haus IPCore. Bit 2: PosReady, Position received and shifted, ready to be read by drive. Bit 3: EncReady, Set once the ic-haus IPCore has been set up and is running. No evaluation of encoder's answers or correctnes of configuration. Bit 4: LastPosValid, Position in last communication cycle was valid. Bit 5: PosValid , Combinated evaluation of Bits -Error (Bit 1 of this status) -nAGSError (Bit 9 of this status) -Position valid from ic-haus core (position received, CRC validated, Bit 12 of this status) -nSCDError (Bit 8 of this status) Bit 6: Bit 7: Bit 8: Bit 9: Bit 10: Bit 11: Bit 12: Bit 13: Bit 14: Bit 15:

CauseRemedy.Cause: Several causes, such as incorrect parameters or incorrect encoder connection to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check encoder status in the parameter list (Encoder actual values)
